               <head>BARTHOLOMEW OF PISA; S. XIV ex. </head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fols. 1–189v)</locus>
                     <author key="person_22494393">BARTHOLOMEW OF PISA OP</author>
                     <title key="work_890">Summa de Casibus Conscientiae</title>
                     <incipit>Quoniam ut ait Gregorius super Ezechiel nullum omnipotenti Deo tale sacrificium est </incipit>
                     <incipit><hi rend="italic">Abbas</hi>. Abbas in suo monasterio conferre potest </incipit>
                     <explicit><note>(<hi rend="italic">Yronia</hi>)</note> est supra inuidia C. secundo.</explicit>
                     <finalRubric>Explicit summa de casibus conscientie secundum compilacionem fratris Bartholomei ordinis predicatorum de Pisis Deo sint gracie infinite.</finalRubric>
                     <note>Pr. Speyer, n. d., Cologne 1474 &amp;c.; Schulte 2. 429 and n. 3; Kaeppeli 436; Bloomfield 5052.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>On fol. 190rv is ‘Penitencia que non datur secundum canones est falsa ... nisi a pena extra de sen. ex tua. (<hi rend="italic">In another hand</hi>) Bartholomeus de casibus’, a series of canons referring to the <hi rend="italic">Decretals</hi>. </note>
                     <note>Fols. 191–2v blank.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
