                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>On <locus>fol. 1</locus> a red and blue initial with flourishing and 3-sided border in the colours; blue initials flourished in red; red or blue paraphs, red underlining.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1700" notBefore="1600">
                        <p>Standard Merton s. xvii, sewn on four bands; formerly chained from the usual position. Fols. i-iii and 193–5 are paper endleaves, the two outermost from the same printed book as in MS 13. On fol. 1 are marks perhaps of two straps and of an iron chain-staple near the foot of the foredge. fol. 192, once a pastedown, has near its foot the marks of the large brass chain-staple.</p>
                     </binding>
