               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1400" notBefore="1375">S. XIV ex.</origDate>
                     <origPlace>script of <country key="place_7002445">English</country> appearance.</origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance notAfter="1556"> The chain-staple mark suggests that the book was at Merton before the Reformation. It was certainly there by 1556 (UO65. 178). </provenance>
                  <provenance>At the head of fol. 1 is the James no. ‘192’ (<hi rend="italic">recte</hi> 189), s. xvii in. </provenance>
                  <provenance>Inside the front board is a sheet of paper with title, s. xvii, ‘F. 6, 5’ (canc.), and ‘O. 4. 2. Art:’, canc. and replaced with ‘H. 2. 12 [<hi rend="italic">corr. to </hi>F. 2. 2]’ and ‘CXLVI)’ in red; the College bookplate. </provenance>
               </history>
